law.text:
The plaintiff named in an action under § 14-866 of this subtitle shall be:
for an action to collect State tax:
the State; or
the Treasurer, or other State officer who is authorized by law to collect the tax;
for an action to collect county tax:
the Mayor and City Council of Baltimore City or the governing body of the county; or
the county collector with a designation of authority;
for an action to collect municipal corporation property tax:
the governing body of the municipal corporation; or
the municipal corporation collector with a designation of authority; or
for an action to collect more than 1 tax from the same person, the collector or other officer who is authorized to collect the taxes.
